The article is a transcript of a press conference where President Obama announces the nomination of Elena Kagan as the next Supreme Court Justice. The President praises Kagan's legal expertise, experience, and leadership qualities, and highlights her commitment to public service. Kagan, in turn, expresses her gratitude for the nomination and discusses her appreciation for the role of the Supreme Court in upholding the Constitution and promoting justice. She also acknowledges the influence of her parents and her dedication to public service. The article concludes with Kagan expressing her eagerness to work with the Senate in the confirmation process.